Guy T. HELVERING, Commissioner of Internal Revenue, v. GREAT AMERICAN LIFE INSURANCE COMPANY. No. 1174. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Feb. 12, 1935. Robert H. Jackson, Asst. Gen. Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. Warren H. White, of Hutchinson, Kan., for respondent.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Petition for review dismissed on motion of petitioner.
